### insertFrom() {#ab0bd3e9464208516b824137ed7c70644}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename KeyT, typename ValT, unsigned N, typename Traits&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>unsigned llvm::IntervalMapImpl::LeafNode&lt; KeyT, ValT, N, Traits &gt;::insertFrom (unsigned &amp; Pos, unsigned Size, KeyT a, KeyT b, ValT y)</>}>
insertFrom - Add mapping of &#91;a;b&#93; to y if possible, coalescing as much as possible.

This may cause the node to grow by 1, or it may cause the node to shrink because of coalescing. 
<ParametersList title="Parameters">

<ParametersListItem name="Size">Number of elements in node.</ParametersListItem>

<ParametersListItem name="y"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> be mapped.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
(insert position, new size), or (i, Capacity+1) on overflow.
</SectionUser>

### safeFind() {#a00c255e0d7969726d82306a392298061}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename KeyT, typename ValT, unsigned N, typename Traits&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>unsigned llvm::IntervalMapImpl::LeafNode&lt; KeyT, ValT, N, Traits &gt;::safeFind (unsigned i, KeyT x) const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
safeFind - Find an interval that is known to exist.

This is the same as findFrom except is it assumed that x is at least within range of the last interval. 
<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="i">Starting index for the search.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="x">Key to search for.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">

</SectionUser>
